article.headline: Alcorn St. 70, MVSU 67
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Troy Jackson scored 23 points and Alex Owumi added 16 as Alcorn State upset Mississippi Valley State 70-67 in overtime Saturday night. The Braves (4-21, 3-10 Southwestern Athletic Conference) snapped a seven-game losing streak by outscoring the Delta Devils (8-15, 6-6) 11-8 in overtime. Anthony Ford added 11 for Alcorn State and Jarvis Williams scored 10. Chris Watson led MVSU with 20 points and 13 rebounds. Dwayne Harmason added 15 points, Carl Lucas scored 12 and Larry Cox added 10.
